        protected <T> T doParse(ParserSession session,
                        ClassMeta<T> type)
                 throws Exception
        Description copied from class: Parser
        Workhorse method. Subclasses are expected to implement this method.
        Specified by:
        doParse in class Parser
        Type Parameters:
        T - The class type of the object to create.
        Parameters:
        session - The runtime session object returned by Parser.createSession(Object, ObjectMap, Method, Object). If null, one will be created using Parser.createSession(Object).
        type - The class type of the object to create. If null or Object.class, object type is based on what's being parsed. For example, when parsing JSON text, it may return a String, Number, ObjectMap, etc...
        Returns:
        The parsed object.
        Throws:
        Exception - If thrown from underlying stream, or if the input contains a syntax error or is malformed.
